Bat populations in Scotland and across the UK have declined considerably over the last century.
These animals are threatened by the construction and development works that affect the dormitories and make the habitat scarce.
Wind turbines and lightning are also a threat, in conjunction with flycatcher papers and some chemical treatments of building materials, in addition to domestic cat attacks.
In fact, bats are not blind.
