This week saw a significant worsening of the situation with new tariffs affecting $200 billion worth of goods (<0xC2><0xA3>150 billion), effectively taxing half of all goods shipped by China to the U.S.
Beijing has always retaliated in the same currency, recently raising rates from 5 to 10 percent for US goods worth $60 billion.
